edu.illinois.ncsa.daffodil.japi

Class WithDiagnostics

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.illinois.ncsa.daffodil.japi.WithDiagnostics
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataProcessor, ParseResult, ProcessorFactory

    public abstract class WithDiagnostics
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract class that adds diagnostic information to classes that extend it.

    When a function returns a class that extend this, one should call isError() or canProceed() on that class before performing any further actions. If an error exists, any use of that class, aside from those functions in WithDiagnostics, is invalid and will result in an Exception.
